            <p>Special Order, From HQ, Floyd's Division,
                  Knoxville. Gen. Floyd relieved of command; regimental
                  commanders to report to Col. George Maney.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Dispatch, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 March 19</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From Col. George Maney; Stuart to hold regiment
                  ready to move and report on the strength of his
                  command.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Military Order, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 March 20</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Stuart directed by Col. Maney to "take command of
                  all the forces here, formerly of Genl Floyd's
                  command, in the movement towards Jacksboro."</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Military Order, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 March 20</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Special order, HQ Knoxville. Stuart to move
                  tomorrow on the road to Clinton.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Military Order, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 March 20</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Special order, HQ Knoxville. Stuart to hold
                  command (36th, 50th, 51st and 56th Virginia
                  Regiments) in readiness to move towards
                  Jacksboro.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Military Order, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 March 21</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>Stuart not to move his command until further
                  orders.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Military Order, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 March 21</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From Col. George Maney. Order to march towards
                  Clinton is revoked.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 March 31</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From Maj. General Marshall, at Lebanon. "...Your
                  vindicating note has been successful, I imagine, in
                  proving that you did not delay marching last winter
                  intentionally, but the failure to join me was a great
                  misfortune to this command. I am ready however to
                  look forward and not backward..."</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 April 1</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>John B. Floyd to Stuart, regarding releasing sick
                  soldier (Hanshew, 50th Virginia Regt) to go home with
                  his father.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 April 8</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>W. R. Abbot to Stuart, requesting recommendation
                  to enter army and relaying family news.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 April 20</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From John B. Floyd, regarding discharge of
                  underage soldier.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 April 30</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From Alfred L. Rives, Acting Chief, Engineering
                  Bureau, Richmond, to Secretary of War George W.
                  Randolph, commending Stuart, with endorsement by
                  Randolph specifically commending his gallantry at
                  Battle of Bethel.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 October 26</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From R. B. Garnett, at Winchester, acknowledging
                  receipt of report of battle of South Mountain and
                  expressing personal regard.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 October 30</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From Thomas D. Jeffress, Provost Marshall's
                  Office, Lynchburg, protesting his possible return to
                  the Regiment.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1862 October 30</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:3</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From George C. Cabell, 18th Virginia Regiment,
                  regarding a report in which he erroneously commended
                  Capt. Jeffress.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1863 March 7</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:4</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>To Gen. Cooper from Lt. F. W. Nelson, Commanding
                  Company A, 56th Virginia, requesting 25 conscripts to
                  fill reduced ranks.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1863 March 7</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:4</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From S. D. Cronin, 1st Lieut. Company I, 56th
                  Virginia Regt., in camp near Petersburg, requesting
                  to be absent from duty to see to business at
                  home.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1863 March 8</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:4</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From F. W. Nelson, Lieut. Company A, 56th Virginia
                  Regt., requesting leave of absence to visit his home
                  in Mecklenburg Co.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Letter, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1863 July 27</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:4</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From Nathaniel A. Flournoy, Co. K, 56th Va., to
                  Stuart, written after the Battle of Gettysburg.
                  Comments on casualties in regiment, wishes Stuart
                  well, hopes he will succeed Gen. Garnett.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item">
          <did>
            <unittitle>Telegram, 
                  <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">April 10, no year</unitdate></unittitle>
            <container label="Box-folder" type="Box-folder">
                  1:4</container>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>From R. L. Owens, Richmond, regarding search of
                  trains for stolen coffee.</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
